{"word":"ἔντροφος","slug":"ἔντροφος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔντροφος</b></el> <el>(ἔντροφος, ον) </el>adj (e)ntrof os_on) <p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐντρέφω'><el>ἐντρέφω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>living in</i> or <i>acquainted with</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, <i>nursling</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}